<div class="sage-type">
  <h2 id="structure">Structure</h2>
  <p>
    The Sage type system uses a minor third modular scale (factor of 1.2) with a base font size of 16pt.
  </p>
  <p>
    Typography in our system uses <code>t-sage-</code> prefixes in order to apply a given typographical specification.
    These can be used on any element to apply the desired typographical styles regardless of the tag. This allows a
    wide range of flexibility for applying a desired style to an element while still using the most semantic element possible
    for a given context.
  </p>
  <p>
    Setting styles individual styles manually should be avoided, but where needed, should be sure to use the appropriate
    <%= link_to "design tokens", pages_token_url %>.
    In the end, we prefer adding new entries to the type spec over including one-off styling.
  </p>
